  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6500.59 sitting above the GEX flip at 6471 in negative gamma territory, dealers are short gamma and forced to chase momentum - they're buying this breakout move and will continue buying rallies while selling any dips back toward 6475. The massive -9.48B gamma wall at 6475 creates an amplification zone where any retreat will trigger aggressive dealer selling, while the positive gamma pocket at 6490 provides temporary resistance as dealers turn into sellers there. \n\nWatch 6475 as the critical support - a break below flips dealers into heavy selling mode, while sustained trade above 6500 keeps dealers buying into strength with next amplifying resistance at 6515's -3B wall.",
